column2: Augmenting cyber threat alerts on the ACES platform with ACES's specific information.
column6: b)  Pilot ¤ The use case has been deployed in a limited test or pilot capacity.
column11: The current Cyberthreat alerts on the ACES platform are difficult to understand and we often see false positives relative to new use cases.
column12:
The current Cyberthreat alerts on the ACES platform are difficult to understand and we often see false positives relative to new use cases. 

We would like to run the alerts through a RAG-enabled AI model to:
‹ Add SEC specific guidance and context to the emails based on a curated knowledge base.
‹ Provide more guidance on how to respond to the alert.
‹ Make the notification email easier to read and understand.
column13: The AI system will output the cyberthreat alert along with information on the context of the threat in the SEC environment.  It will summarize the information and provide suggested guidance in a more readable format.
column19: The ACES team will develop a knowledge base using existing documentation on the workings of the ACES environment in the SEC in order to provide the RAG implementation.
